Of course Judge Bailey don't want these friends of his to suspect that David
                     can fail of getting the appointment by any lack of his influence;
                     for their belief in his influence is his power over them!

"That's the very secret—that's the trade. It's like medicine for the asthma;
                     one medicine don't suit every case; you have to change it according to
                     symptoms."

My friend related what the "intelligent and reliable gentleman" in the toll
                     office had noticed. I heard him through, and then said: "Major, I'm surpised;
                     I'm perfectly astonished at the account you have given!"
